    <text>
        <body xml:id="ch1.sc3.0049">            
                <p><hi rend="initialcap">C</hi>ASE.&#8212;<name type="person" key="350">Private
                        Edward McDole</name>, <name type="organization" key="179">Co. G, 7th New
                            York Heavy Artillery</name>, received, in an engagement before <name type="BATTLE" key="7">Petersburg,
                            Virginia</name>, <date type="injury" when="1864-06-16">June 16th, 1864</date>, a scalp
                    wound, caused by a fragment of shell.  He was admitted to the hospital of the
                    First Division, Second Army Corps; on <date type="transfer" when="1864-06-21">June 21st</date>, he was sent to the <name type="hospital" key="176">Lincoln Hospital</name>, Washington, D. C., and, on <date type="transfer" when="1864-06-28">June 28th</date>, to the <name type="hosptial">Satterlee Hospital, Philadelphia</name>,
                    where he died, on <date type="death" when="1864-07-09">July 9th, 1864</date>,
                    "of hepatitis." </p>            
